---
layout: layouts/page.njk
permalink: /voiceml/compatibility/
title: "VoiceML compatibility matrix"
description: "Enterprise developer comparison of Twilio Programmable Voice, VoiceTel VoiceML, and RestComm on REST resources, voice markup, and migration paths."
---

{%- macro statusBadge(status) -%}
	{%- if status == 'supported' -%}
	<span class="compat-badge compat-supported">Yes</span>
	{%- elif status == 'partial' -%}
	<span class="compat-badge compat-partial">Partial</span>
	{%- elif status == 'unsupported' -%}
	<span class="compat-badge compat-unsupported">No</span>
	{%- else -%}
	<span class="compat-badge compat-roadmap">N/A</span>
	{%- endif -%}
{%- endmacro -%}

<p class="eyebrow">Compatibility</p>
<h1>Compare Twilio, VoiceTel, and RestComm before you migrate voice workloads.</h1>
<p class="lede">Every REST resource and voice markup surface on the VoiceML compatibility matrix is scored side-by-side with Twilio (reference) and RestComm (open-source CPaaS). Use it to see what moves with a hostname swap, what needs markup changes, and what stays out of scope — before you cut traffic over.</p>
<p class="hero-actions">
	<a class="btn btn-primary" href="/voiceml/validator/">Validate VoiceML</a>
	<a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/voiceml/migrate/">Migration guide</a>
</p>

<section id="why-voicetel-built-its-own" class="section-block">
	<h2>Why VoiceTel built its own implementation from scratch</h2>
	<p><strong>Most Twilio-compatible CPaaS platforms in market are not original implementations — they are <a href="https://github.com/RestComm" rel="external">RestComm</a> and their derivatives.</strong> The community open-source RestComm stack ships the compatibility layer that voice and messaging providers then rebrand. VoiceTel authored VoiceML from scratch to make a truly conformant implementation that provides frictionless migration.</p>
</section>

<section id="matrix" class="section-block">
	<h2>Compatibility matrix</h2>
	<p><strong>Legend:</strong>
		<span class="compat-badge compat-supported">Yes</span> &mdash; supported,
		<span class="compat-badge compat-partial">Partial</span> &mdash; partial or documented limitation,
		<span class="compat-badge compat-unsupported">No</span> &mdash; unsupported (404 or 501),
		<span class="compat-badge compat-roadmap">N/A</span> &mdash; out of scope on this surface.
	</p>
	<p>One table per Twilio product. VoiceTel's compatibility surface is grouped the same way Twilio's docs are, so you can pick the product you're migrating and skip to its block.</p>
	<nav class="compat-product-toc" aria-label="Jump to Twilio product">
		<div class="compat-product-toc__grid">
			{%- for product in compatMatrix.products %}
			<a class="compat-product-toc__card" href="#product-{{ product.name | slugify }}">
				<span class="compat-product-toc__name">{{ product.name }}</span>
				<span class="compat-product-toc__meta">{{ product.rowCount }} row{% if product.rowCount != 1 %}s{% endif %} · {{ product.groupCount }} group{% if product.groupCount != 1 %}s{% endif %}</span>
			</a>
			{%- endfor %}
		</div>
	</nav>

	{%- for product in compatMatrix.products %}
	<section id="product-{{ product.name | slugify }}" class="section-block compat-product">
		<h3>{{ product.name }}</h3>
		{%- if product.summary %}
		<p>{{ product.summary | safe }}{% if product.twilioDocsUrl %} <a href="{{ product.twilioDocsUrl }}" rel="external">Twilio docs &rarr;</a>{% endif %}</p>
		{%- elif product.twilioDocsUrl %}
		<p><a href="{{ product.twilioDocsUrl }}" rel="external">Twilio docs &rarr;</a></p>
		{%- endif %}
		<div class="table-container">
			<table class="data-table compat-table compat-table--platforms">
				<thead>
					<tr>
						<th scope="col">Resource</th>
						<th scope="col">Endpoints</th>
						<th scope="col">Twilio</th>
						<th scope="col">VoiceTel</th>
						<th scope="col">RestComm</th>
						<th scope="col">Notes</th>
					</tr>
				</thead>
				<tbody>
					{%- for group in product.groups %}
					{%- for row in group.rows %}
					<tr>
						{%- if loop.first %}
						<th scope="row" rowspan="{{ group.rows | length }}"><strong>{{ group.name | safe }}</strong></th>
						{%- endif %}
						<td class="compat-endpoint">{{ row.endpoints | safe }}</td>
						<td class="compat-status">{{ statusBadge(row.twilio) }}</td>
						<td class="compat-status">{{ statusBadge(row.voicetel) }}</td>
						<td class="compat-status">{{ statusBadge(row.restcomm) }}</td>
						<td class="compat-notes">{{ row.notes | safe }}</td>
					</tr>
					{%- endfor %}
					{%- endfor %}
				</tbody>
			</table>
		</div>
	</section>
	{%- endfor %}
</section>

<aside class="cta-block">
	<h2>Plan your migration</h2>
	<p>The migration guide walks through SDK host overrides, webhook signature validation, signing keys, and per-call cutover for moving compatible voice workloads to VoiceTel.</p>
	<p class="hero-actions">
		<a class="btn btn-primary" href="/voiceml/migrate/">Open migration guide</a>
		<a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/signup/">Sign up</a>
	</p>
</aside>
